title: For Sale:  CHINESE/SHANSI BROOMHANDLE -- MAUSER .45 ACP...Matching/Original...SN911...C&R
location: New Jersey, New Jersey, United States
postcontent: Here's a scarce and original Broomhandle Mauser manufactured by the Nationalist Chinese and chambered for 45 ACP!! These have an interesting history. Prior to WWII Warlord General Yen Hsi-Shan controlled Shansi Province where he commissioned the opening of the Shansi Military Technology Practice Factory. Weapons of any type could be reverse engineered by his craftsmen, the first was the Chinese copy of .45 ACP Thompson submachine gun. The Mauser Broomhandle had always been considered a first rate military handgun in China and Yen decided that a copy chambered in .45 ACP should be produced to compliment his Thompsons. Designated the Type 17, production on the .45 caliber pistol began in 1929. They are inscribed (in Chinese) "Type 17" on the left hand side of the gun, and "Republic Year Eighteen, Made in Shansi" on the right hand side. The Shansi .45 pistols are noticeably larger than their 7.63mm counterparts, with the 10-round magazine extending below the trigger guard. Approximately 8,500 Shansi .45 caliber Broomhandle pistols are believed to have been produced but most were destroyed after the Communist victory in the Chinese Civil War. A few were supplied as military aid to Vietnam in the 1960’s and some offered overseas for sale on the commercial market. This pistol is in very good condition with most of the original finish remaining. There is general fading/thinning but no significant rust or deep pitting. The serial number of this example is "911" and all serial numbered parts are matching. The pistol is import marked. The mechanics appear to be in good working order and the bore is excellent with bright sharp rifling! It comes in a special fitted leather and canvas case and includes a cleaning rod and a stripper clip. These are hard to find and this pistol is far better than most examples that you will encounter.

title: For Sale:  Colt Woodsman Target 2nd Generation
location: North Side of Raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Colt Woodsman Target Model 2nd Generation 
The Gun: The Colt second Generation Woodsman with  6" target barrel was made between 1932 and 1948, serial number 103xxx, so it has the "New and Improved" heat treated mainspring housing.  The bluing and finish according to the S.P. Fjestad Blue Book is 95% , although I do not have original grips or Box .The only shine through the bluing is on the tip if the barrel and the leading edge of the slide.  The Simulated Pearl grips shown  are 1990's vintage, the black rubber grips (2 Pair) are reproduction from the same time frame. The is one original Colt factory 10 shot magazine and one reproduction 10 shot  magazine. The Original leather holster is part of the package and is tight fitting and in good condition. The gun has been rarely shot but is spot on accurate. No parts gun, all numbers match. Close up pictures available for serious buyer.
 The Story: I have owned this gun for 46 years. I bought it from a US Navy shipmate while serving in Viet Nam. Our Destroyer was assigned to Gun Fire Support missions off  the coast  between 1966 and 1968. We would be out to sea for months at a time only to make port for a few days in Yokosuka Japan, Hong Kong or Subic Bay Philippines, then back out to sea. Young Sailors with little liberty would go through money like water. A shipmate of mine desperate for some "R &R Money" offered to sell me this gun. I bought and owned it ever since.
The Deal: In Person sale in or near North Carolina or I will ship  My FFL dealer to Your FFL dealer with a full payment in advance. You pay for shipping and one FFL fee, I will pay the FFL fee on my end. Scammers beware, I will be check out potential buyers and Gun shops.
This is the real McCoy, a real nice Colt Woodsman that you can collect or shoot !

Designed as a specialized option for competition orientated shooters, the Performance Center Custom SW1911 is crafted from the finest components under the skilled hands of master gunsmiths. On top of the slide, an adjustable rear sight and black post front sight aid in precise alignment during competition. Other Performance Center features include a match-grade throated barrel and a Briley spherical bushing for improved accuracy. The Performance Center Custom SW1911 measures 8.7 inches in overall length and has an empty weight of 40.5 ounces.

postcontent: Winchester just announced a recall of two batches of their M*22 line of .22LR ammunition. The lot numbers that are part of the recall are GD42L and GD52L. According to Winchester these lots may have double powder charges which can cause your gun to go kaboom and seriously injure you. If you have any of these batches of ammo DO NOT use them, I know finding .22LR these days is like finding a unicorn, but it’s better to be safe than sorry. More info on the recall can be found below. DO NOT USE WINCHESTER® M*22™ 22 Long Rifle RIMFIRE AMMUNITION WITH LOT NUMBERS GD42L or GD52L. The ammunition Lot Number is imprinted (stamped without ink) on the left tuck flap of the 500-round carton as indicated here. The 1000-round intermediate carton does not have a Lot Number. To determine if your ammunition is subject to this notice, review the Symbol Number and Lot Number. If it is Symbol Number S22LRT with a Lot Number containing GD42L or GD52L immediately discontinue use and contact Winchester toll-free at REDACTED or visit http://www.winchester.com/Product-Service/Pages/Contact-Us.aspx for free UPS pick-up of the recalled ammunition. This notice applies only to Symbol Number S22LRT with Lot Numbers GD42L and GD52L. Other Symbol Numbers or Lot Numbers are not subject to this recall. If you have any questions concerning this 22 Long Rifle rimfire ammunition recall please call toll-free REDACTED, write to Winchester (600 Powder Mill Road, East Alton, IL 62024 Attn: S22LRT Recall), or contact Winchester Customer Support online. - See more at: http://www.thefirearmblog.com/blog/2014/01/29/winchester-recalls-m22-22lr-ammo/#sthash.NJH62eDS.dpuf
